# Obsidian frontmatter — vault conventions

Use **one tag style everywhere**: slash namespaces, lowercase segments, hyphens inside a segment when needed.

| Prefix | Use for | Examples |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `docs/` | Docs bucket by version or kind | `docs/v4`, `docs/howa` |
| `topic/` | Domain or feature theme | `topic/api`, `topic/i18n`, `topic/auth` |
| `tech/` | Concrete stack/tool when the note is primarily about that tech | `tech/nextjs`, `tech/prisma` |
| `project/` | Which vault project the note belongs to | `project/experts`, `project/howa`, `project/logix` |

**Do not** mix `topic-api` / `topic/api` / `docs-v4` / `docs/v4` in the same vault.

**Category** (`category` field): stable string for filtering, e.g. `docs/experts-v4`, `Entity/Tech`, `Projects/Experts/Experts OS`.

**Optional — repo roots (clickable `file://` in notes):** `repo_root` — absolute path to the **package** or repo folder you are documenting (e.g. `/Users/…/projects/experts/apps/experts-app`). Use with [obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc); do not use Markdown relative links for `src/…` paths.

**Linking:** Use **`[[wikilinks]]` only for vault notes**. For code paths, use backticks + “(relative to … root)” — see [obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc).

---

## Experts project docs (`Projects/Experts/Experts App/docs/V*`)

**Minimal schema:** `title`, `date`, `tags`, `category`. Optional: `type` (only if you query/group by it — e.g. `index`, `example`).

- **Automation:** `_tools/apply_experts_docs_frontmatter.py` normalizes all versioned docs (V1–V4). V4 titles/tags can be overridden in `V4_EXPLICIT` inside that script; V1–V3 use inferred tags from folder + `docs/v{n}`.
- **Indexes** `Vn/Vn.md`: regenerated by `_tools/build_experts_version_indexes.py` (do not hand-edit the document list long-term).

---

## Project notes (e.g. `Projects/Experts/Experts OS/*`)

**Minimal schema:** `title`, `date`, `tags`, `category`. Optional: `type` (hubs, symbols, reference — only if useful for queries).

Same tag convention (`docs/…`, `topic/…`, `tech/…`). Prefer tags over duplicating entity topic links in every **Links** section when the goal is filtering.

---

## Experts App GSD planning (`Projects/Experts/Experts App/planning/**`)

**Minimal schema:** `title`, `date`, `tags`, `category`. Optional: `type` (e.g. `index` for the planning hub note `INDEX.md`), `source` / `source_id` when synced from repo, **`repo_root`** / **`monorepo_root`** when the note references `` `apps/experts-app/` `` paths.

- **Wikilinks:** use `[[Projects/Experts/Experts App/planning/...]]` for vault notes under `planning/` (not `.planning/` — that name is **repo-only** under `` `apps/experts-app/.planning/` ``).
- **Repo paths:** backticks + “relative to **experts-app** root” or **monorepo root**; see [obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc).

---

## Entity notes (`Entities/**`)

**Minimal schema:** `title`, `date` (created / first-seen), `tags`, `category` (e.g. `Entity/Tech`, `Entity/Topic`, `Entity/Project`).

Optional: `source`, `source_id` when the row is generated or mirrored from a canonical path. Optional: `repo_root` when the entity note includes `file://` links to a checkout (see [obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc)).

---

## Related rules & tools

- [obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/obsidian-wikilinks-vs-repo-paths.mdc) — wikilinks for vault notes only; backticks + anchor for `src/…` paths.

- `_tools/apply_experts_docs_frontmatter.py` — Experts `docs/V1`–`V4` (optional `--version V4`).
- `_tools/build_experts_version_indexes.py` — rebuilds `V1.md`–`V4.md` indexes.
- `_tools/apply_project_obsidian_frontmatter.py` — HoWA docs/rules, Experts OS, Experts guides/reports/rules + listed Experts root files, Logix, Sulaimani Holdings, Visora, Beyound (does **not** touch `Projects/Experts/Experts App/docs/**`; extend scopes if you want **planning** normalized). **Strict tags are on by default:** bare tokens become `topic/*` or `tech/*` (curated tech list); `topic/<tech-stem>` is rewritten to `tech/<stem>`; use `--no-strict-tags` for legacy behavior. Also: `--dry-run`, `--only howa-docs` (comma-separated scope names) for smaller batches.
